30ProfilerListener::ProfilerListener(Isolate* isolate,
31 CodeEventObserver* observer,
32 CodeEntryStorage& code_entry_storage,
33 WeakCodeRegistry& weak_code_registry,
34 CpuProfilingNamingMode naming_mode)
35 : isolate_(isolate),
36 observer_(observer),
37 code_entries_(code_entry_storage),
38 weak_code_registry_(weak_code_registry),
39 naming_mode_(naming_mode) {}

41ProfilerListener::~ProfilerListener() = default;

43void ProfilerListener::CodeCreateEvent(CodeTag tag, Handle<AbstractCode> code,
44 const char* name) {
45 CodeEventsContainer evt_rec(CodeEventRecord::Type::kCodeCreation);
46 CodeCreateEventRecord* rec = &evt_rec.CodeCreateEventRecord_;
47 PtrComprCageBase cage_base(isolate_);
48 rec->instruction_start = code->InstructionStart(cage_base);
49 rec->entry =
50 code_entries_.Create(tag, GetName(name), CodeEntry::kEmptyResourceName,
51 CpuProfileNode::kNoLineNumberInfo,
52 CpuProfileNode::kNoColumnNumberInfo, nullptr);
53 rec->instruction_size = code->InstructionSize(cage_base);
54 weak_code_registry_.Track(rec->entry, code);
55 DispatchCodeEvent(evt_rec);
56}

73void ProfilerListener::CodeCreateEvent(CodeTag tag, Handle<AbstractCode> code,
74 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared,
75 Handle<Name> script_name) {
76 PtrComprCageBase cage_base(isolate_);
77 CodeEventsContainer evt_rec(CodeEventRecord::Type::kCodeCreation);
78 CodeCreateEventRecord* rec = &evt_rec.CodeCreateEventRecord_;
79 rec->instruction_start = code->InstructionStart(cage_base);
80 rec->entry =
81 code_entries_.Create(tag, GetName(shared->DebugNameCStr().get()),
82 GetName(InferScriptName(*script_name, *shared)),
83 CpuProfileNode::kNoLineNumberInfo,
84 CpuProfileNode::kNoColumnNumberInfo, nullptr);
85 rec->entry->FillFunctionInfo(*shared);
86 rec->instruction_size = code->InstructionSize(cage_base);
87 weak_code_registry_.Track(rec->entry, code);
88 DispatchCodeEvent(evt_rec);
89}

93CodeEntry* GetOrInsertCachedEntry(
94 std::unordered_set<CodeEntry*, CodeEntry::Hasher, CodeEntry::Equals>*
95 entries,
96 CodeEntry* search_value, CodeEntryStorage& storage) {
97 auto it = entries->find(search_value);
98 if (it != entries->end()) {
99 storage.DecRef(search_value);
100 return *it;
101 }
102 entries->insert(search_value);
103 return search_value;
104}

108void ProfilerListener::CodeCreateEvent(CodeTag tag,
109 Handle<AbstractCode> abstract_code,
110 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared,
111 Handle<Name> script_name, int line,
112 int column) {
113 CodeEventsContainer evt_rec(CodeEventRecord::Type::kCodeCreation);
114 CodeCreateEventRecord* rec = &evt_rec.CodeCreateEventRecord_;
115 PtrComprCageBase cage_base(isolate_);
116 rec->instruction_start = abstract_code->InstructionStart(cage_base);
117 std::unique_ptr<SourcePositionTable> line_table;
118 std::unordered_map<int, std::vector<CodeEntryAndLineNumber>> inline_stacks;
119 std::unordered_set<CodeEntry*, CodeEntry::Hasher, CodeEntry::Equals>
120 cached_inline_entries;
121 bool is_shared_cross_origin = false;
122 if (IsScript(shared->script(cage_base), cage_base)) {
123 Handle<Script> script =
124 handle(Script::cast(shared->script(cage_base)), isolate_);
125 line_table.reset(new SourcePositionTable());
126
127 is_shared_cross_origin = script->origin_options().IsSharedCrossOrigin();
128
129 bool is_baseline = abstract_code->kind(cage_base) == CodeKind::BASELINE;
130 Handle<TrustedByteArray> source_position_table(
131 abstract_code->SourcePositionTable(isolate_, *shared), isolate_);
132 std::unique_ptr<baseline::BytecodeOffsetIterator> baseline_iterator;
133 if (is_baseline) {
134 Handle<BytecodeArray> bytecodes(shared->GetBytecodeArray(isolate_),
135 isolate_);
136 Handle<TrustedByteArray> bytecode_offsets(
137 abstract_code->GetCode()->bytecode_offset_table(), isolate_);
138 baseline_iterator = std::make_unique<baseline::BytecodeOffsetIterator>(
139 bytecode_offsets, bytecodes);
140 }
141 // Add each position to the source position table and store inlining stacks
142 // for inline positions. We store almost the same information in the
143 // profiler as is stored on the code object, except that we transform source
144 // positions to line numbers here, because we only care about attributing
145 // ticks to a given line.
146 for (SourcePositionTableIterator it(source_position_table); !it.done();
147 it.Advance()) {
148 int position = it.source_position().ScriptOffset();
149 int inlining_id = it.source_position().InliningId();
150 int code_offset = it.code_offset();
151 if (is_baseline) {
152 // Use the bytecode offset to calculate pc offset for baseline code.
153 baseline_iterator->AdvanceToBytecodeOffset(code_offset);
154 code_offset =
155 static_cast<int>(baseline_iterator->current_pc_start_offset());
156 }
157
158 if (inlining_id == SourcePosition::kNotInlined) {
159 int line_number = script->GetLineNumber(position) + 1;
160 line_table->SetPosition(code_offset, line_number, inlining_id);
161 } else {
162 DCHECK(!is_baseline);
163 DCHECK(IsCode(*abstract_code, cage_base));
164 std::vector<SourcePositionInfo> stack =
165 it.source_position().InliningStack(isolate_,
166 abstract_code->GetCode());
167 DCHECK(!stack.empty());
168
169 // When we have an inlining id and we are doing cross-script inlining,
170 // then the script of the inlined frames may be different to the script
171 // of |shared|.
172 int line_number = stack.front().line + 1;
173 line_table->SetPosition(code_offset, line_number, inlining_id);
174
175 std::vector<CodeEntryAndLineNumber> inline_stack;
176 for (SourcePositionInfo& pos_info : stack) {
177 if (pos_info.position.ScriptOffset() == kNoSourcePosition) continue;
178 if (pos_info.script.is_null()) continue;
179
180 line_number =
181 pos_info.script->GetLineNumber(pos_info.position.ScriptOffset()) +
182 1;
183
184 const char* resource_name =
185 (IsName(pos_info.script->name()))
186 ? GetName(Name::cast(pos_info.script->name()))
187 : CodeEntry::kEmptyResourceName;
188
189 bool inline_is_shared_cross_origin =
190 pos_info.script->origin_options().IsSharedCrossOrigin();
191
192 // We need the start line number and column number of the function for
193 // kLeafNodeLineNumbers mode. Creating a SourcePositionInfo is a handy
194 // way of getting both easily.
195 SourcePositionInfo start_pos_info(
196 isolate_, SourcePosition(pos_info.shared->StartPosition()),
197 pos_info.shared);
198
199 CodeEntry* inline_entry = code_entries_.Create(
200 tag, GetFunctionName(*pos_info.shared), resource_name,
201 start_pos_info.line + 1, start_pos_info.column + 1, nullptr,
202 inline_is_shared_cross_origin);
203 inline_entry->FillFunctionInfo(*pos_info.shared);
204
205 // Create a canonical CodeEntry for each inlined frame and then re-use
206 // them for subsequent inline stacks to avoid a lot of duplication.
207 CodeEntry* cached_entry = GetOrInsertCachedEntry(
208 &cached_inline_entries, inline_entry, code_entries_);
209
210 inline_stack.push_back({cached_entry, line_number});
211 }
212 DCHECK(!inline_stack.empty());
213 inline_stacks.emplace(inlining_id, std::move(inline_stack));
214 }
215 }
216 }
217 rec->entry = code_entries_.Create(
218 tag, GetFunctionName(*shared),
219 GetName(InferScriptName(*script_name, *shared)), line, column,
220 std::move(line_table), is_shared_cross_origin);
221 if (!inline_stacks.empty()) {
222 rec->entry->SetInlineStacks(std::move(cached_inline_entries),
223 std::move(inline_stacks));
224 }
225
226 rec->entry->FillFunctionInfo(*shared);
227 rec->instruction_size = abstract_code->InstructionSize(cage_base);
228 weak_code_registry_.Track(rec->entry, abstract_code);
229 DispatchCodeEvent(evt_rec);
230}

233void ProfilerListener::CodeCreateEvent(CodeTag tag, const wasm::WasmCode* code,
234 wasm::WasmName name,
235 const char* source_url, int code_offset,
236 int script_id) {
237 CodeEventsContainer evt_rec(CodeEventRecord::Type::kCodeCreation);
238 CodeCreateEventRecord* rec = &evt_rec.CodeCreateEventRecord_;
239 rec->instruction_start = code->instruction_start();
240 rec->entry = code_entries_.Create(tag, GetName(name), GetName(source_url), 1,
241 code_offset + 1, nullptr, true,
242 CodeEntry::CodeType::WASM);
243 rec->entry->set_script_id(script_id);
244 rec->entry->set_position(code_offset);
245 rec->instruction_size = code->instructions().length();
246 DispatchCodeEvent(evt_rec);
247}
248#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY

335void ProfilerListener::CodeDeoptEvent(Handle<Code> code, DeoptimizeKind kind,
336 Address pc, int fp_to_sp_delta) {
337 CodeEventsContainer evt_rec(CodeEventRecord::Type::kCodeDeopt);
338 CodeDeoptEventRecord* rec = &evt_rec.CodeDeoptEventRecord_;
339 Deoptimizer::DeoptInfo info = Deoptimizer::GetDeoptInfo(*code, pc);
340 rec->instruction_start = code->instruction_start();
341 rec->deopt_reason = DeoptimizeReasonToString(info.deopt_reason);
342 rec->deopt_id = info.deopt_id;
343 rec->pc = pc;
344 rec->fp_to_sp_delta = fp_to_sp_delta;
345
346 // When a function is deoptimized, we store the deoptimized frame information
347 // for the use of GetDeoptInfos().
348 AttachDeoptInlinedFrames(code, rec);
349 DispatchCodeEvent(evt_rec);
350}

362const char* ProfilerListener::GetName(base::Vector<const char> name) {
363 // TODO(all): Change {StringsStorage} to accept non-null-terminated strings.
364 base::OwnedVector<char> null_terminated =
365 base::OwnedVector<char>::New(name.size() + 1);
366#if defined(__GNUC__) && !defined(__clang__)
367 // Work around a spurious GCC-12 warning (-Werror=array-bounds).
368 if (name.end() < name.begin()) return nullptr;
369#endif
370 std::copy(name.begin(), name.end(), null_terminated.begin());
371 null_terminated[name.size()] = '\0';
372 return GetName(null_terminated.begin());
373}
374
375Tagged<Name> ProfilerListener::InferScriptName(
376 Tagged<Name> name, Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> info) {
377 if (IsString(name) && String::cast(name)->length()) return name;
378 if (!IsScript(info->script())) return name;
379 Tagged<Object> source_url = Script::cast(info->script())->source_url();
380 return IsName(source_url) ? Name::cast(source_url) : name;
381}

383const char* ProfilerListener::GetFunctionName(
384 Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> shared) {
385 switch (naming_mode_) {
386 case kDebugNaming:
387 return GetName(shared->DebugNameCStr().get());
388 case kStandardNaming:
389 return GetName(shared->Name());
390 default:
391 UNREACHABLE();
392 }
393}

395void ProfilerListener::AttachDeoptInlinedFrames(Handle<Code> code,
396 CodeDeoptEventRecord* rec) {
397 int deopt_id = rec->deopt_id;
398 SourcePosition last_position = SourcePosition::Unknown();
399 int mask = RelocInfo::ModeMask(RelocInfo::DEOPT_ID) |
400 RelocInfo::ModeMask(RelocInfo::DEOPT_SCRIPT_OFFSET) |
401 RelocInfo::ModeMask(RelocInfo::DEOPT_INLINING_ID);
402
403 rec->deopt_frames = nullptr;
404 rec->deopt_frame_count = 0;
405
406 for (RelocIterator it(*code, mask); !it.done(); it.next()) {
407 RelocInfo* info = it.rinfo();
408 if (info->rmode() == RelocInfo::DEOPT_SCRIPT_OFFSET) {
409 int script_offset = static_cast<int>(info->data());
410 it.next();
411 DCHECK(it.rinfo()->rmode() == RelocInfo::DEOPT_INLINING_ID);
412 int inlining_id = static_cast<int>(it.rinfo()->data());
413 last_position = SourcePosition(script_offset, inlining_id);
414 continue;
415 }
416 if (info->rmode() == RelocInfo::DEOPT_ID) {
417 if (deopt_id != static_cast<int>(info->data())) continue;
418 DCHECK(last_position.IsKnown());
419
420 // SourcePosition::InliningStack allocates a handle for the SFI of each
421 // frame. These don't escape this function, but quickly add up. This
422 // scope limits their lifetime.
423 HandleScope scope(isolate_);
424 std::vector<SourcePositionInfo> stack =
425 last_position.InliningStack(isolate_, *code);
426 CpuProfileDeoptFrame* deopt_frames =
427 new CpuProfileDeoptFrame[stack.size()];
428
429 int deopt_frame_count = 0;
430 for (SourcePositionInfo& pos_info : stack) {
431 if (pos_info.position.ScriptOffset() == kNoSourcePosition) continue;
432 if (pos_info.script.is_null()) continue;
433 int script_id = pos_info.script->id();
434 size_t offset = static_cast<size_t>(pos_info.position.ScriptOffset());
435 deopt_frames[deopt_frame_count++] = {script_id, offset};
436 }
437 rec->deopt_frames = deopt_frames;
438 rec->deopt_frame_count = deopt_frame_count;
439 break;
440 }
441 }
